            "Door Step Service": `<span class="important-note">Requirements:</span><br>- 1-Take the call from the registered number and confirm the service needed is one of the three listed on Note.<br>- 2- Check the system (T-24/CRM) to confirm the customer is flagged as a Senior Citizen or Disabled.<br>- 3-Inform the Customer: Advise them that their main branch will contact them to schedule the visit. Assure them the staff will show a CIB ID for verification.<br>- 4-Assign & Confirm: Submit the request in CRM, directing it to the customer's main branch. Remind the customer that the visit can only be to their registered address.<br><span class="important-note">NOTE:</span><br>- Purpose: To provide banking services at home for Senior Citizens (65+) and Disabled Customers.<br>- Eligible Services:<br>- KYC information updates.<br>- Activating dormant accounts (if the customer has no other active account).<br>- Account closure requests.`,
            "Escalation Call": `<span class="important-note">Requirements:</span><br>- Customer insists on contacting a Supervisor.<br>- Customer wants to investigate another agent for attitude, wrong information, etc.<br>- Smart Script must be used.<br>- Proper and detailed case description is required.<br>- In investigation cases, the CP# and the date & time of the original call are mandatory.<br><span class="important-note">NOTE:</span><br>- (TAT): X (To be determined based on internal policy).<br>- Prime & PLUS = Throughout the day if the order is placed before 4 PM.<br>- Wealth & Privat = 2 hours`,
            "Escalation Call to Quality": `<span class="important-note">Requirements:</span><br>- When to Assign:<br>- Waiver issues<br>- System/behavior issues (call placed on hold for more than 2 minutes, call dropped/disconnected, etc.)<br>- Agent attitude problems<br>- Incorrect information provided by the agent, but the issue was resolved by the CRU team  <br>*Used the below template*<br>Customer insist to assign request to hear the call regarding ( Cisco behavior - Agent Attitude-Waiver due to agent mistake -Wrong Info ).<br>• Date of Incident:<br>• Calling Party:<br>• Account / Fake Account: <br>• Copy of TRX (Transaction ID): <br>• Masked CC (If Applicable): <br>• Detailed Description of the Issue:<br>• Corrective Action Taken (if any):<br><span class="important-note">NOTE:</span><br>- This task is for the escalation team only.<br>- TAT :2 WD`,
            "Overseas Call": `<span class="important-note">Requirements:</span><br>- Overseas Coding Process<br><br>Egyptian Customer (with valid residency abroad)<br><br>If KYC and ID are valid, the agent should instruct the customer to send an email to<br>Overseas.Support@cibeg.com<br>, attaching their residency permit,<br>to be coded as Overseas.<br><br>Foreigner Customer<br><br>If requirements are met, the agent should also direct the customer to email<br>Overseas.Support@cibeg.com<br> requesting Overseas coding.<br><br>Egyptian Customer (resident abroad but no foreign address)<br><br>Agent should first help the customer change their mailing address<br>through the normal address update process over the call.<br><br>Then instruct the customer to send an email to<br>Overseas.Support@cibeg.com<br> attaching their residency permit.<br><br>If an Overseas Customer contacts the center for service<br><br>Only specific remote services are available per their segment<br>(list of services follows in the next section).<br><span class="important-note">NOTE:</span><br>- Callback Request (Wealth Coding)<br>- SLA:<br>- If Back Office receives the email from the Overseas Distribution Team before 2:00 p.m., processing will be same working day.<br>- If received after 2:00 p.m., it will be handled next working day.`,
            "PCA Verification": `<span class="important-note">Requirements:</span><br>- Call must be from the PCA's registered mobile number.<br>- PCA must verify: ( All this date on PCA sheet )<br>- Full name<br>- NID<br>- Ccomputer number<br>- Windows password.<br><span class="important-note">NOTE:</span><br>- Handle inquiries from a PCA (Private Customer Advisor) about their assigned private client.<br>- Assign the request under the customer’s profile, not the PCA’s profile.`,
