            "Re-Allocation - Credit Card": `<span class="important-note">Requirements:</span><br>- Check System (Shift + F7): There is a negative (-ve) amount in either the Retail or Cash sub-account.<br>- Customer Reports: The customer receives a specific error when trying to make a transaction, indicating that the card limit is only available in a ""specific group"" (e.g., only for retail or only for cash).<br><span class="important-note">NOTE:</span><br>- In simple terms: Assign this request when the card's limit is ""stuck"" in the wrong category (retail/cash), showing a negative balance in one sub-account and preventing the customer from using their available credit normally.<br>-We don’t assign re-allocation requests any more. The card is re-allocated normally in the beginning of the new statement.`
